# Projocalypse — delete confirmation dialogs

All **user-initiated delete** actions in the UI must show an in-app confirmation dialog before persisting the delete. Do not call `window.confirm()` for deletes.

Related: **`projocalypse-tailwind-shadcn.mdc`**, **`projocalypse-real-implementation.mdc`**.

## Required pattern

| Piece | Location |
|-------|----------|
| Primitives | `src/components/ui/alert-dialog.tsx` (Radix Alert Dialog) |
| Shared wrapper | `ConfirmDialog` in `src/components/ui/confirm-dialog.tsx` |
| Usage | Local `open` state; menu/button sets `open` to `true`; `onConfirm` calls the Dexie delete in `src/db/operations.ts` |

```tsx
const [deleteOpen, setDeleteOpen] = useState(false)

<DropdownMenuItem onClick={() => setDeleteOpen(true)}>Delete …</DropdownMenuItem>

<ConfirmDialog
  open={deleteOpen}
  onOpenChange={setDeleteOpen}
  title={`Delete "${entity.name}"?`}
  description="Explain what is removed and that it cannot be undone."
  confirmLabel="Delete project"
  destructive
  onConfirm={() => deleteProject(entity.id)}
/>
```

## Applies to

- Delete **project**, **section**, **task**, **subtask**
- Any new UI that permanently removes stored entities

Set `destructive` and a specific `confirmLabel` (e.g. `"Delete task"`) on irreversible deletes.

## Does not apply

- Test code and non-UI scripts
- Sync/tombstone cleanup inside `src/db/` or `src/lib/sync/` (not user-triggered)
- **Bulk replace** flows (import over live data) — use `ConfirmDialog` too, but wording differs; see **`projocalypse-mission-critical.mdc`**

## When adding a delete control

1. Add `ConfirmDialog` with clear title + description (name the entity; state scope of loss).
2. Wire the destructive menu/button to open the dialog, not to delete directly.
3. Never ship `window.confirm()` for delete paths in `src/components/`.
